[[Vice-Admiral]] '''Peter William Cairns''' [[Order of Military Merit (Canada)|CMM]] (born October 4, 1938) is a retired officer of the [[Canadian Forces]]. He was [[Commander of the Royal Canadian Navy|Commander Maritime Command]] from 1992 to 1994.

==Career==
Cairns joined the [[Royal Canadian Navy]] in 1956 and was appointed a [[midshipman]] in 1959.<ref name=naut>[http://nauticapedia.ca/dbase/Query/Biolist3.php?name=Cairns,%20Peter%20William&id=10532&Page=1&input=Cairns,%20Peter%20William Peter Cairns] The Nauticapedia</ref> He became Commanding Officer of the [[submarine]] {{HMCS|Onondaga|S73|6}} in 1972, Commander of the First Canadian Submarine Squadron in 1974 and Commanding Officer of the [[destroyer]] {{HMCS|Fraser|DDH 233|6}} in 1976.<ref name=naut/> He went on to command the destroyers {{HMCS|Margaree|DDH 230|6}} in 1977 and {{HMCS|Assiniboine|DDH 234|6}} in 1978. He became Deputy Commandant of the Canadian Forces Fleet School at [[Halifax Regional Municipality|Halifax]] in 1978.<ref name=naut/> After that he was appointed Chief Project Technical Officer at Canadian Forces Maritime Command in 1979, Commandant of the Canadian Forces Maritime Warfare School later that year and Commander Fifth Canadian Destroyer Squadron in 1981.<ref name=naut/> Next he became Chief of Personnel Careers (Officers and Senior Appointments) at the [[National Defence Headquarters (Canada)|National Defence Headquarters]] in 1983, Director-General Personnel Careers (Officers) in 1985 and Deputy Chief of Staff (Operations) to the [[Supreme Allied Commander Atlantic]] in 1987.<ref name=naut/> His last appointments were as Commander [[Maritime Forces Pacific]] in 1989 and as [[Commander of the Royal Canadian Navy|Commander Maritime Command]] in 1992 before he retired in 1994.<ref name=naut/>

In retirement Cairns became Director of Business Development at the Aviation Services Division of [[Spar Aerospace]].<ref>[http://www.cfnconsultants.com/pcairns.shtml Peter Cairns] CFN Consultants</ref>

